Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
deleteShield(25.10)                                        deleteShield(25.10)

Name
       deleteShield  -  Deletes physical shielding wires from the specified or
       selected signal nets and removes SHIELDNET attributes from the nets

Syntax
       deleteShield

       [-help]

       {-nets <list_of_signal_nets> | -selected}

       [-routes_only {0 | 1}]

       Deletes physical shielding wires from the specified or selected  signal
       nets   and   removes  SHIELDNET  attributes  from  the  nets.  Use  the
       deleteShield command after setting the SHIELDNET attribute on a net. To
       set the SHIELDNET attribute, use the setAttribute command.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information  for each deleteShield parameter. For a detailed de-
              scription of the command and all of its parameters, use the  man
              command

              man deleteShield

       -nets <list_of_signal_nets>
              Specifies  a  list of signal nets with one or more SHIELDNET at-
              tributes. You can use the  asterisk  (*)  wildcard  in  the  net
              names.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -routes_only {0 | 1}
              Specifies that only shield wires and vias will be deleted.

              Data_type: enum, optional

       -selected
              Lets you select nets.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Examples
              * The  following command deletes SHIELDNET attributes and physi-
                cal shielding wires from net clk1:

                deleteShield -nets clk1

              * The following command deletes SHIELDNET attributes and  physi-
                cal shielding wires from nets c*:

                deleteShield -nets c*

              * The  following command deletes SHIELDNET attributes and physi-
                cal shielding wires from selected nets:

                deleteShield -selected

